&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Please note that at the current time Ward 11 is temporarilybeing utilised as a Covid admission assessment area.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ward 11 Intermediate Care is seeking dedicated and enthusiastic Staff Nurses to join our well established integrated team. We are currently a 30 bedded unit that specialises in rehabilitation and integrated care. Our patients benefit from having a dedicated therapy team based on the unit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We welcome all candidates that are committed to providing patients with high standards of quality care as well as particular interest in elderly care. The majority of our patients have complex health needs both medical and surgical.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is suitable for either newly qualified or experienced nurses.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidates will have the opportunity to learn, develop and practice a variety of skills in both rehabilitation and acute nursing, as well as being a valued member of our exceptional multidisciplinary team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are interested in this position then we encourage you to make contact with Sister Jane Watson or Sister Hannah Kelly on 01625 661 011 for an informal chat and/or informal visit to the unit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This post is Permanent&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours per week: 37.5 (part-time, flexible working and rotations will also be considered)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Shift patterns: shifts will be either early (7:00-15:00), late (13:00-20:00), long day (7:00-20:00) or night shifts (19:30-7:30).&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date: 19th November 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please be aware that this post requires an Enhanced Disclosure and Barring Service (DBS) check, the cost of which is payable by the successful candidate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you have lived or worked abroad for 6 months or more in the last 5 years you will need to obtain an overseas police clearance. Further information can be found on the additional information links at the bottom of the advert.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;To keep up to date with all of our latest Recruitment activity here at East Cheshire NHS Trust, take a look at our Facebook and Twitter pages, links to which can be found on the right hand side:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Visit our Facebook page: Careers at East Cheshire NHS Trust&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Follow us on Twitter: @CareersECT&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For details about the role and ward/informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Anisha Jijo, Senior Sister Ward 11&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Anisha.jo@nhs.net&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;01625 661011&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For queries regarding the application and or interview process, please contact the Recruitment Team either via email, ecn-tr.recruitment@nhs.net or telephone, 01625 656510&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We would like to inform you that if your application is successful, your interview will be held via SKYPE.&lt;/p&gt;
